Kim Jong Il Inspects Several Production Units of KPA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected several production units run by the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, Jang Song Thaek, department director of the C.C., WPK, Ri Yong Chol and Ri Jae Il, first deputy department directors of the C.C., WPK, and KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his inspection was the cotton plantation under KPA Unit 1596. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being briefed on the plantation, he looked round vast cotton fields to acquaint himself in detail with its trial cotton cultivation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He appreciated the successes made by the plantation, noting that the tenacious efforts made by the plantation have resulted in systematically increasing the production and accumulating not a few experience necessary for putting the cotton farming on a scientific basis in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the master key to the successful cultivation of cotton to solve the issue of seed, he noted, underscoring the need to pay special attention to the research and introduction of high-yielding strain requiring a short period for growth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that it is possible to boost the yield while using less materials and manpower only when farming is placed on a scientific and technical basis as required by bioengineering, he stressed that it is important to actively introduce advanced methods of farming while rounding off the Korean-style system of cultivation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his inspection was the new cotton processing factory built by KPA servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Walking round production processes, he learnt in detail about the technical equipment and production there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to keep the production going at a high rate, it is necessary to steadily improve the control of equipment and technical management and incessantly raise the level of technical skills of the producers, he said, setting forth the tasks to be implemented by the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last leg of his inspection was the exhibition of products turned out by the combined building materials factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the building materials on display are very high in their quality, he said that the construction of the new combined building materials factory with big production capacity has made it possible to bring about a qualitative leap forward in the field of construction in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be carried out by the factory to keep the production there going at a high rate and build up it under a long-term plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called upon all the leading officials to minutely organize everything and push ahead with it in a tenacious manner by displaying the revolutionary fighting spirit just as the commanding officers of the KPA do and thus enable the people to lead a more affluent life as early as possible.

Personal Letter to Kim Jong Il from U.S. President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a personal letter from George W. Bush, President of the United States of America. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter was conveyed to DPRK Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun on Wednesday by Christopher Hill, U.S. assistant secretary of State who visited the DPRK.

DPRK Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Recovery from Flood Damage 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the DPRK today gave the following answer to the question raised by KCNA as regards the successful progress made by the DPRK in the efforts to recover from the flood damage in a brief span of time: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As already known, our country as a whole was hit by unprecedented torrential rain and strong wind in August last that caused big casualties and material losses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government made every possible effort to eradicate the aftermath of the disaster by mobilizing all forces. As a result, the country brought the living of the people in all the afflicted areas to normal and prevented the outbreak of infectious diseases and rehabilitated in the main the houses, factories, enterprises and farm land and power network, railways, roads, bridges and other infrastructure left submerged or destroyed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The medicines, food and other relief materials sent by the United Nations and other international organizations, different countries and organizations as emergency aid helped the Korean people facilitate the work to recover from the flood damage in a short period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK feels grateful for this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will continue to make efforts to boost the cooperation with international organizations and different countries in the future, too.

Kim Yong Nam Receives Credentials from Zambian Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received credentials from Lupando A. F. K. Mwape, Zambian ambassador to the DPRK, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After receiving the credentials, Kim had a talk with the ambassador.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Zambian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by Zambian President Levy Patrick Mwanawasa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was handed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, by Lupando A. F. K. Mwape, Zambian ambassador newly accredited to the DPRK, on Thursday.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Lao Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the delegation of officials in charge of foreign affairs of the Lao People's Army on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was handed to an official concerned by Siphay Munduang, director of the External Relations Department of the Ministry of Defence, who is leading the delegation.

New Type of Air Sterilizing Purifier Developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- The State Academy of Sciences of the DPRK has of late developed a new type of air sterilizing purifier. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The purifier using nano photocatalyst sterilizes and dissolves various pathogenic bacilli and poisonous gas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@An experiment found that the purifier completely purified dozens of cubic meters of room air in 30 minutes and the germ-free condition was maintained during its operation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The purifying material made through the application of nano technology can be used nearly semipermanently. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Its cost of production is much lower than the former one and the consumption of electricity is 25 to 30 watts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The purifier is being introduced into hospitals, families and office rooms.

Environment Fund Engaged in Wide Range of Activities 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- The Korean Natural Environment Conservation Fund (abbreviation; environment fund) is engaged in a wide range of activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Nowadays the fund is supporting the establishment of an environmental knowledge dissemination centre as part of environmental propaganda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The centre called "Environmental House of Children" is to provide school youth and children with comprehensive knowledge about environmental problems including general knowledge of environment, environmental observation and sample analysis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@While supporting the tentative construction of dwelling houses and villages using renewable energies, it has worked out a plan for "the protection of migratory birds and their habitats" involving the Rajin-Sonbong area of North Hamgyong Province and the Kumya area of South Hamgyong Province which are habitats of the migratory birds flying between Australia and New Zealand and Siberia of Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It has also marked off areas to be afforested in the country and is pushing ahead with cooperation with environmental organizations of different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The fund is bending efforts for the protection and proliferation of the Korean tigers and the white-bellied black woodpeckers and plants registered as indigenous species of the country like Abeliophyllum distichum which is of single family and single species. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It registers individual persons and organizations that have made contributions to environmental protection as its members, honorary members or honorary directors and issues appropriate certificates to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Korean Natural Environment Conservation Fund founded in March Juche 94 (2005) has a large number of members.

All Members of Society Called upon to Learn from Soldier Culture
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- The Korean People's Army is playing the role of a pacemaker in developing culture in the Songun era and the revolutionary soldier culture serves as a model culture for all members of the society. Herein lies the essential characteristics of the socialist cultural construction in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in an editorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the intention and will of the Workers' Party of Korea to make the revolutionary enthusiasm and militant spirit, optimism and emotion of the People's Army prevail throughout the country and help all the people become genuine creators and enjoyers of socialist culture in the Songun era, the editorial notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The soldier culture reflects the spirit of the present times, fixed faith in and optimism about victory in the revolution and militant enthusiasm, joy and rich emotion. It has served as a powerhouse as it helped effect a revolutionary turn in the Korean people's ideological and moral traits and cultural and emotional life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was through the drive to learn from the revolutionary spirit and lifestyle of the People's Army that the Korean people emerged those strong in faith and optimists who cheerfully pull through any hardships and ordeals and the whole country was pervaded with revolutionary enthusiasm free from stagnation and standstill, hesitation or vacillation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people can enjoy a worthwhile life as genuine creators and enjoyers of socialist culture when they always carve out a noble life full of faith in certain victory and optimism just as servicepersons do. This is the truth the Korean people have learned in practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All party members and other working people should steadily intensify the work to learn from the revolutionary soldier culture as required by the era in which they are working hard to achieve the great prosperity of the country and thus bring about full efflorescence in the cultural construction in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest pride and honor of the Korean people to have such a model for the socialist cultural construction as the revolutionary soldier culture.

All Koreans Called upon to Preserve Spirit of National Independence
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- The Korean people have firmly maintained the stand of attaching importance to the nation in the struggle to bring about the heyday of the cause of independent reunification in response to the militant appeal of the joint editorial this year.  Rodong Sinmun Thursday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The patriotic enthusiasm of the Koreans that has grown strong since the outset of the year helped bring about a new turn in the efforts to achieve the reunification of the country and national prosperity in the strong spirit of national independence of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north and the south and overseas came to have strong consciousness of national independence that it is the only the Korean nation that can settle the issue of national reunification as it is responsible for the issue. This is the most precious success. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole land of three thousand ri resounded throughout the year with loud voices calling for national independence, i.e. the assertion that either peace of the country or development of inter-Korean relations and reunification and prosperity of the nation should be achieved by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The same voices could be heard from the meeting of north and south Korean workers for reunification. The participants of the meeting for the great unity of the nation marking the 7th anniversary of the June 15 joint declaration strongly called for holding fast to the stand of attaching importance to the nation in settling the issue of reunification in the idea of "By our nation itself" free from the interference and pressure of the anti-reunification forces at home and abroad and protecting the interests of the nation and giving full play to the might of the driving force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These calls for national independence made by all Koreans in the north and the south and overseas reflecting their patriotic will and desire were a manifestation of their high awareness and will to perform their responsibilities and roles as a driving force for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is nothing impossible for the Korean nation when all its members have such strong spirit of national independence as the determination to conduct the movement for national reunification while rejecting flunkeyism and dependence upon foreign forces and firmly believing in the nation's strength and relying on it, concludes the article.

Abolition of NSL Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- A rally on the "day of all-people action for repealing the National Security Law" (NSL) was reportedly held in Seoul on December 1, 59 years after the draconian NSL was cooked up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending it were members of civic and social organizations of different circles including the People's Solidarity for the Repeal of the NSL and more than 1,000 victims of the law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the rally charged that the NSL is an anti-reunification and undemocratic law, a copy of the "Maintenance of the Public Order Act" under the Japanese imperialist rule over Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "There can be no new society unless the NSL is abolished," they noted, calling upon the people from all walks of life to intensify the all-people actions for the repeal of the evil law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration read out at the rally said that traitor Ri Hoe Chang can never escape a stern judgement of the people as he has cried out for inter-Korean confrontation, dead-set against the repeal of the NSL. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It warned that they will wage a positive movement to defeat those "presidential" candidates who are opposed to the repeal of the evil law, defying the demand of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration released on the same day a statement titled "Let us repeal the National Security Law, the leftover of the old era, and take the lead in the struggle to eliminate the Cold War-minded conservative forces."

Evening for Reunification Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 6 (KCNA) -- The Federation of south Korean Trade Unions reportedly held an evening for reunification in Seoul on December 3 on the theme of the "Implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Yong Duk, chairman of the federation, in his speech at the event said that the reunification movement for putting an end to the tragic national division is naturally part of the labor movement, declaring that the workers would take the lead in the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 O Jong Ryol, co-chairman of the Solidarity for Progress of south Korea, Ri Sok Haeng, chairman of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions, and others who took the floor to express solidarity said that the Federation of south Korean Trade Unions and the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions should narrow down each other's differences and achieve concord in the course of jointly carrying out the tasks for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon the workers to firmly unite and advance in the June 15 era in which Koreans are striving to achieve reunification in the spirit of "By our nation itself".

Tienen lugar conversaciones de expertos militares Norte-Sur
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kaesong, 5 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Segun el acuerdo de la segunda ronda de las conversaciones entre los ministros de las Fuerzas Armadas del Norte y el Sur de Corea tuvieron lugar el dia 5 en el pabellon Thong-il de la parte norcoreana de Phanmunjom las conversaciones de expertos militares entre ambas partes para asegurar de manera militar el transporte ferroviario de cargas Munsan-Pongdong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A la cita asistieron los miembros de la delegacion nortena encabezada por el primer coronel del Ejercito Popular de Corea Pak Rim Su y los de la delegacion surena presidida por el coronel Mun Song Muk como delegado-jefe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion fue aprobado el acuerdo para el aseguramiento militar del citado transporte ferroviario.

MINREX se refiere a la recuperacion de danos por inundaciones
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 6 de diciembre (ATCC) -- En una entrevista exclusiva con la Agencia Telegrafica Central de Corea, el portavoz de la cancilleria de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea hizo este jueves las siguientes declaraciones en relacion con que en nuestro pais se llevo a cabo exitosamente en un corto plazo la recuperacion de los danos ocasionados por inundaciones: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Como ya trascendidos, en agosto ultimo, se reportaron grandes perdidas humanas y materiales debido al inusitado aguacero y fuertes turbonadas que azotaron toda la extension de nuestro pais. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El gobierno de la RPDC realizo ingentes esfuerzos movilizando todas las fuerzas, de manera que se estabilizo en sentido general la vida de los habitantes de zonas damnificadas y quedo prevenido el brote de epidemias. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas se recuperaron fundamentalmente en su estado original las viviendas, fabricas, empresas y tierras cultivables, que habian sido anegadas o destruidas, y las instalaciones de infraestructura como la red de transmision electrica, ferrocarril, carretera y puente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los materiales de socorro como medicamentos y alimentos, que donaron a titulo de cooperacion emergente la ONU y otras organizaciones internacionales y varios paises y entidades, contribuyeron a que el pueblo coreano pudiera terminar en un corto periodo el resarcimiento de los danos por inundaciones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Nuestro pais esta muy agradecido del respecto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Al igual que en el pasado, nuestro pais seguira esforzandose por fortalecer y desarrollar la colaboracion con las organizaciones internacionales y otros paises.

Embajador zambio entrega cartas credenciales a Kim Yong Nam 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 6 de diciembre (ATCC) -- El presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, recibio este jueves en el capitalino Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae las cartas credenciales de Lupando A. F. K. Mwape que le acreditan como nuevo embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario de la Republica de Zambia en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A continuacion, Kim departio con el diplomatico.
